
[1]monitor

   MON'ITOR, n. [L.] One who warns of faults or informs of duty; one who
   gives advice and instruction by way of reproof or caution.

   You need not be a monitor to the king.

   1. In schools, a person authorized to look to the scholars in the
   absence of the instructor, or to notice the absence of faults of the
   scholars; or to instruct a division of class.
